Bollywood singer Udit Narayan Jha found himself in a controversy on Thursday (February 12, 2026) after his first wife, Ranjana Jha, recently filed a complaint at a women’s police station in the Supaul district of north Bihar. She levelled charges that her uterus was removed without her consent during an operation in 1996 in Delhi by her husband, Udit Narayan Jha, and his two brothers.

Ranjana Jha, in her complaint to the police, said that she was married to Udit Narayan Jha on December 7, 1984 under Hindu rituals.

Also Read |Singer Udit Narayan faces backlash after video shows him kissing female fan at live concert

Accompanied by her lawyer, Karunakant Jha, Ranjana Jha, 61, the daughter of Chandrakant Jha, approached the women’s police station in the Supaul district of north Bihar, where she has been a resident, on Tuesday (February 10, 2026).  She further claimed that she became aware of the operation years later, during a medical consultation.

According to her, Udit Narayan Jha moved to Mumbai in 1985 to pursue his singing career in Bollywood. However, she later learned through media reports that he had married another woman, Deepa Narayan. Every time he was questioned about this, he “kept misleading her.”

In 1996, under the pretext of medical treatment, Ranjana Jha claimed that Udit Narayan Jha and his two brothers, Sanjay Kumar Jha and Lalit Narayan Jha, took her to a large hospital in Delhi, where her uterus was surgically removed without her consent.

